  "playingCareerSummary": "Former Australia batting all-rounder: 8 Tests, 76 ODIs (1987-1999). Part of the 1987 and 1999 ODI World Cup winning Australia squads. Did not play in the IPL.",
  "bio": "One of the most prolific and successful T20 franchise head coaches ever — 11 IPL seasons across two franchises with one championship. Inaugural head coach of Kings XI Punjab (2008-2010), taking them to the 2008 semi-finals. Joined Sunrisers Hyderabad in 2013 as their inaugural head coach and served two stints (2013-2019, 2022), delivering SRH's maiden IPL title in 2016 (beating RCB by 8 runs in the final) and another final appearance in 2018. Also served as Director of Cricket at SRH during 2015-2019. Stepped down from his second stint on 2 September 2022 and was replaced by Brian Lara.",
